body:
From the 7.15 Patch notes:

&quot;Ekko fares pretty well against mages when his cooldowns are up, so we&#039;re giving him the tools to engage more often.&quot;

Does this mean that Riot acknowledges the fact that champions can be fairly balanced or leaning toward the strong side, but they buff them just because?

Some buffs just have no way to justify them. That quote has essentially become a meme at this point for its utter stupidity and lack of any logic whatsoever. Why would you buff champions for no reason anyway? This thread isn&#039;t about the Ekko buff itself, moreso the apparent meaning behind that quote.

&quot;Annoying champion does this pretty well, so we&#039;re giving annoying champion the tools to be annoying more often. We&#039;ll maybe possibly sometimes give annoying champion a nerf of -1 base health to compensate so we don&#039;t overdo it.&quot;

Seems to be Riot&#039;s logic. Balanced champions (or as close as can be) don&#039;t need buffs.
